                            <comment id="13051605" author="stack" created="Sat, 18 Jun 2011 22:08:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch looks good.  What do you think the implications of notifyAll on everything were Karthick?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13051631" author="karthick" created="Sun, 19 Jun 2011 03:16:27 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;What do you think the implications of notifyAll on everything were Karthick?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Basically, it would notify all calls, even those that may have arrived less than the timeout period ago. that they timed out. FWIW, if you don&apos;t use timeouts, then you won&apos;t run into this issue.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13052277" author="karthick" created="Mon, 20 Jun 2011 23:29:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I forgot to port a small yet critical change - the &lt;tt&gt;cleanupCalls(long rpcTimeout)&lt;/tt&gt; needs to be synchronized so as to block out any concurrent &lt;tt&gt;addCall(Call)&lt;/tt&gt; methods.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
